%N A348484 Maximum number of squares on an n X n chessboard such that no two are two steps apart horizontally or vertically.
%C A348484 The sequence 1, 4, 5, 8, 13, ... with g.f. -x*(1 +2*x -2*x^2 +2*x^3 +x^4)/ ((1+x) *(x^2+1) *(x-1)^3) and a(n)= 2*a(n-1) -a(n-2) +a(n-4) -2*a(n-5) +a(n-6) is a lower bound for a(n) achieved by packing 2x2 squares with 1's and 2x2 squares with 0's in a checkerboard pattern into the chessboard. - _R. J. Mathar_, Dec 03 2022
%F A348484 Conjectures:
%F A348484 a(n) = n^2/2 for n == 0 (mod 4).
%F A348484 a(n) = (n^2 + 1)/2 for n == 1 or 3 (mod 4).
%F A348484 a(n) = n^2/2 + 2 for n == 2 (mod 4).
